(40, 1, '2011-09-20 20:59:20', '2011-09-20 20:59:20', '<div class="event-2-col-wide">\r\n<div class="event-col-left">\r\n<h3>WHAT ARE PRIVATE-PUBLIC SCREENINGS</h3>\r\nLulacruza and Vincent Moon welcome all our listeners and followers to host their own screenings of Esperando el Tsunami.\r\n\r\nWe call these screenings <strong>Private-Public Screenings</strong> and the rules are very simple.\r\n\r\nThere is a few rules to follow:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><strong>The screenings need to have free entrance</strong></li>\r\n	<li><strong>The screenings need to be public.</strong></li>\r\n	<li><strong>The screenings need to have a minimum capacity of 5 people</strong></li>\r\n	<li><strong>The screenings need to be verified by Vincent Moon and Lulacruza, only screenings that are featured on <a href="http://www.esperando.cc" target="_blank">esperando.cc</a> are official screenings</strong></li>\r\n</ul>\r\nIn other words as long as entrance is free and it is an open event (as capacity permits) the <strong>Private-Public Screenings</strong> can take place in your home, at a café, in a school auditorium or any place you can think of.\r\n\r\nThe <strong>Private-Public Screenings</strong> will run for three months – <strong>November 25th 2011 to February 29th 2012</strong>. The screenings are private because they are hosted by private people and public because the screenings are official and open to anyone – hence the name <strong>Private-Public Screenings</strong>.\r\n\r\n<em>"We hope that a lot of people will host and attend screenings of Esperando el Tsunami. Inspired by the greatly successful release of An Island, we choose to release The Private-Public Screenings are our attempt at creating a free and inspiring distribution method for our film. It is also our attempt to give something back to our many supporters around the world. We have financed this film ourselves and we hope that we can recoup some of that money through donations. However, the memory of the 4 days we spent on the island of Als in August 2010 and our joy and pride of the finished film is a huge reward in itself." – Vincent Moon &amp; Efterklang</em>\r\n<h3>HOW DOES IT WORK – TECHNICALLY SPEAKING?</h3>\r\nAs a host you will receive a personal link to a download package. This download package will provide you with the film in high resolution as a .mov file type. The download package has a size of 1,6GB. We will use TransferBigFiles.com to handle the files.\r\n\r\nIf you would like to use a <strong>DVD player</strong> to screen the film then you can burn a playable DVD using a DVD burner application and the film file in the download package.\r\n\r\nYou can either connect it to a projector or one of those modern TVs, or simply screen it on your computer´s screen.\r\n\r\n<strong>An Island is a music film. We encourage you to make sure that you can screen the film properly and with good and clear sound.</strong>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="event-col-right">\r\n<h3>SIGN UP TO HOST A PRIVATE-PUBLIC SCREENING</h3>\r\n\r\nThis is where you sign up to host a <strong>Private-Public Screening</strong>, but first we recommend you read the rules and introduction on the left.\r\n\r\nOnce you submit your details we will verify them as fast as possible and we will notify you by email once the screening is announced on www.esperando.cc. <strong>Please notice that we need 11 days minimum to approve you screening and get you the files.</strong>\r\n\r\nIf you represent a venue, cinema, festival or any other form of organization in the cultural and entertainment world and you are interested in setting up a screening, then please contact<a href="mailto:esperandoeltsunami@gmail.com">esperandoeltsunami@gmail.com</a> to get info about hosting <strong>Official Screenings</strong>.\r\n\r\n[lulacruza-button href="/screening/host-a-screening" text="click here to create a private-public screening"]\r\n<h3>HOW DO PEOPLE ATTEND?</h3>\r\nThe hosts of Private-Public Screenings can invite friends and strangers to their screenings any way they prefer.\r\n\r\nIn addition to this it will be possible for anyone to contact the host of a screening in the Attend a Screening section on this site. Here people can request to be invited for a Private-Public Screening.\r\n\r\nIf you plan on hosting a screening in your home you have full control over who shows up. If you only have room for 5 people and you already know who these 5 people will be – then you can mark your Private-Public Screening as fully booked already when creating the event. It is also optional for you to decide if the street name and number of the screening is visible or not in the Attend a Screening section.\r\n\r\nHowever, please remember that the screenings are public. If space permits we encourage the host to welcome anyone who asks for an invitation. When there is no room for more guests the host can log in to www.anisland.cc and change the status of the screening to fully booked.\r\n\r\nVincent Moon and Efterklang will both help spread the word about the many screenings via Twitter and Facebook. We encourage hosts to announce their events and spread the word about An Island and the Private-Public Screenings via their social networks and personal websites if possible.\r\n<div>\r\n<h3>COPYRIGHT</h3>\r\nExcept where otherwise noted, all content relating to An Island is licensed under a<strong>Creative Commons</strong> <a href="http://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Attribution-NonCommercial-Share Alike 3.0 License</a>. For more information please visit: <a href="http://creativecommons.org/about/licenses/">creativecommons.org/about/licenses/</a>\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>', 'HOST A PUBLIC-PRIVATE SCREENING', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'host-a-screening-description', '', '', '2011-11-04 17:28:11', '2011-11-04 17:28:11', '', 29, 'http://localhost:8888/lulacruza/?page_id=40', 0, 'page', '', 0),
