(116, 1, '2011-10-18 20:37:12', '2011-10-18 20:37:12', '<div class="scrn-col-left">\r\n<h3>WHAT ARE PRIVATE-PUBLIC CONCERTS</h3>\r\n<strong>Lulacruza invites all of our listeners and followers to host us for a concert at their own space.</strong>\r\n\r\nWe call these events <strong>Private-Public Concerts</strong> (P/P Concerts). The concept is simple: P/P Concerts are <a href="http://www.lulacruza.com" target="_blank">Lulacruza</a> performances held at small gatherings that are organized by people in their homes, community centers, art galleries, collective spaces, etc. You can request to host a concert through our website, and we will provide you with a tool kit to help you as you organize the event in your community. We are very excited to introduce this program, which allows  micro-communities of people to collaborate over distances in order to create something happen collectively!\r\n\r\nThe rules are very simple:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><strong>The concert needs to be public.</strong></li>\r\n	<li><strong>The concert needs to have a minimum capacity of 25 people.</strong></li>\r\n	<li><strong>The hosts will work collaboratively with us to ensure the best possible experience.</strong></li>\r\n	<li><strong>The concert will be verified and approved by Lulacruza. Only events that are featured on <em>www.esperando.cc</em> will be official Private-Public Concerts.</strong></li>\r\n</ul>\r\nIn other words, as long as the gathering is held at a public event (as capacity permits) the <strong>Private-Public Concerts</strong> can take place in your home, at a café, in a church, in a community center, at a school auditorium...at virtually any place you can think of.\r\n\r\nThe <strong>Private-Public Concerts</strong> will be held during 2012 – starting in March.\r\n\r\n<em>“We hope that people are inspired to host and attend these Private-Public Concerts. Influenced by Efterklang and Vincent Moon’s Private-Public Screenings, the P/P Concerts are our attempt at creating a healthy, sustainable touring method that creates a direct link between the audience and the performer and gives Lulacruza the opportunity to go to places ‘off the tour grid,’ reaching new audiences and sharing the necessary tools for clusters of people to organize their own community events. We want the audience and the performer to share equally as co-creators of the experience. We imagine a tour in which we connect with rural and urban micro-communities around the world and share in a richer experience than the current possibilities of touring and performing allow for.”</em> - Lulacruza\r\n<h3></h3>\r\n<h3>SIGN UP TO HOST A PRIVATE-PUBLIC CONCERT</h3>\r\nInterested in participating in the Private-Public Concert series? This is where you sign up! But before you complete the forms, we recommend you read the rules and introduction above.\r\n\r\nOnce you submit your details, you will receive an auto-reply stating that we have received your request. Before approving your request we will contact you via email to discuss the details for your proposed concert. After your event is approved, we will notify you via email, announce it on <em>www.esperando.cc</em>, send you an event toolkit (which will include fundraising tools) and work with you to help organize the best event possible.\r\n\r\n<strong>Please understand that while Lulacruza would like to accept every offer for a Private-Public Concert, it will not always be possible for us to visit every host that we connect with. Distance, timing and travel costs are important factors that will determine where and when we will be able to perform. In most cases it will take months to coordinate each concert; from the moment you make your request, until the moment we perform at your space. Also, please consider that we can only be in one place at a time, so we encourage you to submit your proposal as early as possible to ensure the availability of your desired date.</strong>\r\n\r\nIf you represent a venue, festival or cultural institution and would like to host a Lulacruza concert, please contact <a href="mailto:esperandoeltsunami@gmail.com">esperandoeltsunami@gmail.com</a> to get info about hosting an Official Lulacruza Concert.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h3>HOW DO PEOPLE ATTEND?</h3>\r\nThe hosts of <strong>Private-Public Concerts</strong> can invite friends and strangers to their concerts any way they prefer.\r\n\r\nFurthermore,  it will be possible for anyone to contact the host of a concert in the <a title="Attend a Concert" href="http://localhost:8888/lulacruza/concerts/attend-a-concert/">Attend a Concert</a> section of this site. Here, people can request to be invited to a <strong>Private-Public Concert.</strong>\r\n\r\n<strong>If you plan on hosting a concert in your home, you have full control over who shows up.</strong> If you only have room for 25 people and you already know who these 25 people will be, then you can mark your Private / Public Concert as already being <strong>fully booked</strong> when creating the event. It is also optional for you to decide if the street name and number of the concert is visible or not in the <a title="Attend a Concert" href="http://localhost:8888/lulacruza/concerts/attend-a-concert/">Attend a Concert</a> section.\r\n\r\nHowever, please remember that these are intended to be public events. If space permits, we encourage the host to welcome anyone who asks for an invitation. When there is no room for more guests, the host can log in to <em>www.esperando.cc</em> and change the status of the concert to <strong>fully booked</strong>.\r\n\r\n<strong>Vincent Moon</strong> and <strong>Lulacruza</strong> will both help spread the word about these events via <strong>Twitter</strong> and <strong>Facebook</strong>. Additionally, we encourage hosts to announce their events and spread the word about <strong>Esperando el Tsunami</strong> and the <strong>Private-Public Concerts</strong> via their social networks and personal websites if possible.\r\n\r\nWe hope to start building a <strong>Collectives Network</strong> around this project, a community of people who choose to “host” a screening or concert will have the option of joining this Network, allowing them to share their information and connect with other collectives who have been moved by similar ideas and objectives.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h3>HOW DOES IT WORK – LOGISTICALLY &amp; TECHNICALLY SPEAKING?</h3>\r\nOnce your event has been approved, you will receive a personal link to download an event toolkit. This download package will provide you with all the  information you need to get your event off of the ground, including: how to build collaborative volunteer groups; how to create a space that is inviting and appropriate for the event; how to satisfy the technical and logistical requirements of the event; how to promote your event; and how to fund-raise or sell tickets for the event.\r\n\r\nUnlike Private-Public Screenings - where we can send you a file anywhere in the world in minutes - <strong>Private-Public Concerts</strong> requires bringing Lulacruza and their one-of-a-kind performance to your space. We are aware that this will involve travel, logistical and technical costs. But don’t worry, we are keeping these costs to a minimum, and trying to keep P/P Concerts accessible for everyone. Each concert will have a set price determined by regional currencies and values, travel distance and costs, venue size and the number of people that may attend, as well as the number of shows in nearby regions and locations. Our toolkit will offer a few channels and methods that can help you raise the necessary funds, as well as information on how to choose the option that best fits your particular needs and circumstances. We will also help spread the word  to try and make all approved concerts possible.\r\n\r\nWe will also be assisting you by email throughout the process, to help develop technical, logistical, economic and promotional solutions.\r\n\r\n<strong>The Private-Public Concerts are an opportunity for us to work together in creative cohesion, celebrating the diversity of people and experiences in this interdependent community. We look forward to working with you in order to deliver a rewarding creative experience for all parties involved...and to deliver a meaningful concert experience for the audience!</strong>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h3>COPYRIGHT</h3>\r\nExcept where otherwise noted, all content relating to Esperando el Tsunami is licensed under a <strong>Creative Commons</strong> <a href="http://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Attribution-NonCommercial-Share Alike 3.0 License</a>. For more information please visit:<a href="http://creativecommons.org/about/licenses/"> creativecommons.org/about/licenses/</a>\r\n\r\n</div>', 'Host a Concert', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'host-a-concert-description', '', '', '2011-11-01 19:59:00', '2011-11-01 19:59:00', '', 101, 'http://localhost:8888/lulacruza/?page_id=116', 0, 'page', '', 0),
(117, 1, '2011-10-18 20:37:03', '2011-10-18 20:37:03', '<div class="scrn-col-left">\n<h3>THE PRIVATE-PUBLIC CONCERTS</h3>\n<p>The idea is simple – in february and march 2011, with the project <a href="http://www.anisland.cc">AN ISLAND</a> made with the band <a href="www.efterklang.net">Efterklang</a>, we experimented a new way to show the film – by letting people host their own screenings, where they wanted. The success was quite unexpected, and gave me the idea to continue to show my films in such a way.</p>\n\n<p>From now on, you are welcome, through this page, to organize your own screening of ANY of my films, where you desire, when you want.</p>\n\n<p>There is a few rules to follow:</p>\n\n<ul>\n<li>The screenings need to have free entrance.</li>\n<li>The screenings need to be public.</li>\n<li>The screenings need to have a minimum capacity of 5 people.</li>\n<li>The screenings need to be verified by Vincent Moon and only screenings that are featured on <a href="petitesplanetes.cc">petitesplanetes.cc</a> are official screenings.</li>\n<li>The screenings can take place in your home, at a café, in a school auditorium, in a bar, in the streets… Any place, really.</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p>I hope you will enjoy seeing the films in such a way. You are welcome to pick any film i have made over the years, and not only the ones from Petites Planetes. You can even ask me for some unreleased ones – the complete list of films is on <a href="http://vincentmoon.com/">vincentmoon.com</a></p>\n\n\n<h3>HOW DOES IT WORK – TECHNICALLY SPEAKING</h3>\n<p>I upload all my films on vimeo – <a href="http://vimeo.com/vincentmoon/videos">vimeo.com/vincentmoon/videos</a></p>\n\n<p>You can download the films in good quality from there.</p>\n\n<p>If you would like to use a DVD player to screen the film then you can burn a playable DVD using a DVD burner application.</p>\n\n<p>You can either connect it to a projector or one of those modern TVs, or simply screen it on your computer´s screen.</p>\n\n<p>My films very often contains MUSIC. So it will be better if you get a very good sound system – its often more important than the quality of the image.</p>\n\n\n<h3>COPYRIGHT</h3>\n<p>Except where otherwise noted, all content relating to All my Work is licensed under a Creative Commons Attribution-NonCommercial-Share Alike 3.0 License. For more information please visit: <a href="http://www.creativecommons.org/about/licenses/">creativecommons.org/about/licenses/</a></p>\n</div>\n\n<div class="scrn-col-right">\n<h3>SIGN UP TO HOST A PRIVATE-PUBLIC SCREENING</h3>\n<p>This is where you sign up to host a Private-Public Screening, but first we recommend you to read the rules and introduction on the left.\n\n<p>Once you submit your details we will verify them as fast as possible and we will notify you by email once the screening is announced on www.petitesplanetes.cc.\n\n<span class="btn-text"><a href="http://localhost:8888/lulacruza/screening/host-screening">CLICK HERE TO CREATE A PRIVATE-PUBLIC SCREENING</a></span>\n<h3>HOW DO PEOPLE ATTEND?</h3>\n<p>The hosts of private-public screenings can invite friends and strangers to their private-public screenings any way they prefer.</p>\n\n<p>In addition to this it will be possible for anyone to contact the host of a screening in the section on this site. Here people can request to be invited for a screening.</p>\n\n<p>If you plan on hosting a screening in your home you have full control over who shows up. If you only have room for 5 people and you already know who these 5 people will be – then you can mark your screening as fully booked already when creating the event. It is also optional for you to decide if the street name and number of the screening is visible or not.</p>\n\n<p>However, please remember that the private-public screenings are public. If space permits we encourage the host to welcome anyone who asks for an invitation. When there is no room for more guests the host can log in to <a href="http://petitesplanetes.cc/">petitesplanetes.cc</a> and change the status of the screening to fully booked.</p>\n\n<p>I will help spread the word about the private-public screenings via Twitter and Facebook. And you are of course encouraged to announce your event and spread the word via your social networks and personal websites if possible.</p>\n</div>', 'Host a Concert', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '116-revision', '', '', '2011-10-18 20:37:03', '2011-10-18 20:37:03', '', 116, 'http://localhost:8888/lulacruza/116-revision/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
