(254, 3, '2011-11-03 23:01:26', '2011-11-03 23:01:26', '<div class="event-col-left">\r\n<h3>WHAT''S THE DIFFERENCE?</h3>\r\n<strong>Private-Public Screenings </strong>will run from <strong><em>November 25th 2011 - February 29th 2012</em></strong>. Anyone can host a screening and the rules for Private-Public Screenings are very simple. The screenings needs to be public and have a minimum capacity of 5 people and free entrance. <strong>Private-Public Screenings</strong> can take place in people''s homes, at cafés, in libraries – pretty much anywhere. You can read more about them at <a title="HOST A PUBLIC-PRIVATE SCREENING" href="http://localhost:8888/lulacruza/screenings/host-a-screening-description/">Host a Screening</a>.\r\n\r\n<strong>Official Screenings</strong> are hosted by venues, cinemas, festivals or other players in the cultural and entertainment world. They can be free, they can have an entrance fee, they can be part of film festivals or concerts.\r\n<h3>official screenings</h3>\r\nFollow us on facebook and twitter to be updated about new official screenings.\r\n<div class="event-group">\r\n<div class="event-month">February</div>\r\n<ul class="official-events">\r\n	<li>\r\n<div class="event-summary"><span class="event-date">10.02</span> - <span class="event-location">Basel, CH</span> / <span class="event-venue">1.Stock</span> / <span class="event-price">free entrance</span></div></li>\r\n	<li>\r\n<div class="event-summary"><span class="event-date">10.02</span> - <span class="event-location">Basel, CH</span> / <span class="event-venue">1.Stock</span> / <span class="event-price">free entrance</span></div></li>\r\n	<li>\r\n<div class="event-summary"><span class="event-date">10.02</span> - <span class="event-location">Basel, CH</span> / <span class="event-venue">1.Stock</span> / <span class="event-price">free entrance</span></div></li>\r\n	<li>\r\n<div class="event-summary"><span class="event-date">10.02</span> - <span class="event-location">Basel, CH</span> /