(264, 6, '2011-11-03 21:22:32', '2011-11-03 21:22:32', '[lulacruza-icon name="circle-star"]\r\n<p style="font-size: 22px;">welcome</p>\r\na film by\r\n<span class="sans">VINCENT MOON</span>\r\n<div class="giant-title">ESPERANDO\r\n<span class="italic">el</span> TSUNAMI</div>\r\nan album by\r\n<span class="sans">LULACRUZA</span>\r\n<p class="bigger">A traveling visual album that lies\r\nin between music and cinema.</p>\r\nEsperando el Tsunami <em>(Waiting for the Tsunami)</em> is a quest for the sounds and people of present-day Colombia,\r\nin a continuous improvisation by the filmmaker and musicians as we composed and created on the road.\r\n\r\n[lulacruza-icon name="wave"]\r\n<div class="btn-rect btn-rect-sm read-more">read more</div>\r\n[lulacruza-latest-news-item title="latest news" fallback="no news found at this time" more="..."]\r\n\r\n[lulacruza-btn-top title="top"]', 'ESPERANDO EL TSUNAMI', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '9-revision-18', '', '', '2011-11-03 21:22:32', '2011-11-03 21:22:32', '', 9, 'http://localhost:8888/lulacruza/9-revision-18/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(265, 6, '2011-11-03 21:51:14', '2011-11-03 21:51:14', '[lulacruza-icon name="shell"]\r\n<div class="small-title">ESPERANDO\r\n<span class="italic">el</span> TSUNAMI</div>\r\n\r\n<div class="divider-top-sm">&nbsp;</div>\r\n\r\n<p style="font-size:22px;"><b>the film</b></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="font-size:19px;">"An intoxicating picture &amp; sound piece disguised as a road movie"</p>\r\n\r\n“Vincent Moon is back with what he calls his best film ever. We are not reluctant to agree \r\nwith him… Lulacruza travel across Colombia to take the country’s musical nectar and \r\ntransform it into their almost shamanic trance sessions, Moon follows closely with his\r\nsensuous-seeking camera and responsive musicianship... \r\n\r\nA magical-realism love story of the most beautiful kind." CPH:DOX\r\n\r\nOfficial Selection for the Sound and Vision Award \r\n<div class="btn-rect btn-rect-lg">visit our vimeo channel</div>\r\n[lulacruza-latest-news-item title="latest news" fallback="no news found at this time" more="..."]\r\n\r\n[lulacruza-btn-top title="top"]', 'THE FILM ', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '11-revision-31', '', '', '2011-11-03 21:51:14', '2011-11-03 21:51:14', '', 11, 'http://localhost:8888/lulacruza/11-revision-31/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(266, 2, '2011-11-03 23:19:02', '2011-11-03 23:19:02', '<div class="event-col-left">\r\n<h3>WHAT ARE PRIVATE-PUBLIC SCREENINGS</h3>\r\nLulacruza and Vincent Moon welcome all our listeners and followers to host their own screenings of Esperando el Tsunami.\r\n\r\nWe call these screenings <strong>Private-Public Screenings</strong> and the rules are very simple.\r\n\r\nThere is a few rules to follow:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><strong>The screenings need to have free entrance</strong></li>\r\n	<li><strong>The screenings need to be public.</strong></li>\r\n	<li><strong>The screenings need to have a minimum capacity of 5 people</strong></li>\r\n	<li><strong>The screenings need to be verified by Vincent Moon and Lulacruza, only screenings that are featured on <a href="http://www.esperando.cc" target="_blank">esperando.cc</a> are official screenings</strong></li>\r\n</ul>\r\nIn other words as long as entrance is free and it is an open event (as capacity permits) the <strong>Private-Public Screenings</strong> can take place in your home, at a café, in a school auditorium or any place you can think of.\r\n\r\nThe <strong>Private-Public Screenings</strong> will run for three months – <strong>November 25th 2011 to February 29th 2012</strong>. The screenings are private because they are hosted by private people and public because the screenings are official and open to anyone – hence the name <strong>Private-Public Screenings</strong>.\r\n\r\n<span style="text-decoration: underline;"><em>"We hope that a lot of people will host and attend screenings of Esperando el Tsunami. Inspired by the greatly successful release of An Island, we choose to release The Private-Public Screenings are our attempt at creating a free and inspiring distribution method for our film. It is also our attempt to give something back to our many supporters around the world. We have financed this film ourselves and we hope that we can recoup some of that money through donations. However, the memory of the 4 days we spent on the island of Als in August 2010 and our joy and pride of the finished film is a huge reward in itself." – Vincent Moon &amp; Efterklang</em></span>\r\n<h3></h3>\r\n<h3>SIGN UP TO HOST A PRIVATE-PUBLIC SCREENING</h3>\r\nI upload all my films on vimeo – <a href="http://vimeo.com/vincentmoon/videos">vimeo.com/vincentmoon/videos</a>\r\n\r\nYou can download the films in good quality from there.\r\n\r\nIf you would like to use a DVD player to screen the film then you can burn a playable DVD using a DVD burner application.\r\n\r\nYou can either connect it to a projector or one of those modern TVs, or simply screen it on your computer´s screen.\r\n\r\nMy films very often contains MUSIC. So it will be better if you get a very good sound system – its often more important than the quality of the image.\r\n<h3>COPYRIGHT</h3>\r\nExcept where otherwise noted, all content relating to All my Work is licensed under a Creative Commons Attribution-NonCommercial-Share Alike 3.0 License. For more information please visit: <a href="http://www.creativecommons.org/about/licenses/">creativecommons.org/about/licenses/</a>\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="event-col-right">\r\n<h3>SIGN UP TO HOST A PRIVATE-PUBLIC SCREENING</h3>\r\nThis is where you sign up to host a Private-Public Screening, but first we recommend you to read the rules and introduction on the left.\r\n\r\nOnce you submit your details we will verify them as fast as possible and we will notify you by email once the screening is announced on www.petitesplanetes.cc.\r\n\r\n[lulacruza-button href="http://localhost:8888/lulacruza/screening/host-a-screening" text="click here to create a private-public screening"]\r\n<h3>HOW DO PEOPLE ATTEND?</h3>\r\nThe hosts of private-public screenings can invite friends and strangers to their private-public screenings any way they prefer.\r\n\r\nIn addition to this it will be possible for anyone to contact the host of a screening in the section on this site. Here people can request to be invited for a screening.\r\n\r\nIf you plan on hosting a screening in your home you have full control over who shows up. If you only have room for 5 people and you already know who these 5 people will be – then you can mark your screening as fully booked already when creating the event. It is also optional for you to decide if the street name and number of the screening is visible or not.\r\n\r\nHowever, please remember that the private-public screenings are public. If space permits we encourage the host to welcome anyone who asks for an invitation. When there is no room for more guests the host can log in to <a href="http://petitesplanetes.cc/">petitesplanetes.cc</a> and change the status of the screening to fully booked.\r\n\r\nI will help spread the word about the private-public screenings via Twitter and Facebook. And you are of course encouraged to announce your event and spread the word via your social networks and personal websites if possible.\r\n\r\n</div>', 'HOST A PUBLIC-PRIVATE SCREENING', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '40-revision-17', '', '', '2011-11-03 23:19:02', '2011-11-03 23:19:02', '', 40, 'http://localhost:8888/lulacruza/40-revision-17/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
